Class GUI3DModels

java.lang.Object
  provider.GUI3DModels
Direct Known Subclasses:
GUI3DModelsSimple
public class GUI3DModels
extends java.lang.Object

The GUI3DModels-provider provides logic for loading all 3D-Object into memory and then providing information about them.

Version:
20120627
Author:
langenhagen

setup

public static final void setup(processing.core.PApplet pApp,
                               java.lang.Class<? extends GUI3DModels> clazz,
                               java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String> rootDirectories)
Sets the 3D-models up and initializes the provider itself. Therefore it should be called once at the beginning of your program. Sets up the GUI3DModels-singleton to an instance of of a given GUI3DModels (Sub-)Class.

Parameters:
pApp - The Application to render the fonts as a PApplet.
clazz - The Class GUI3DModels or some Class which extends it.
rootDirectories - An Iterable of type String that contains all root directories where the factory can find resources.

loadModel

public void loadModel(java.lang.String path)
Loads a model at the specified path and maintains it in this provider's memory, along with a key. If a model with the same key is already stored, it will be overridden.

Parameters:
path - The full path to the 3D-model as a String.

Parameters:

variant - The variant to set as an int.
scaleToUnitVal - The multiplicator when the model whill be scaled to unit as a float.

unloadModel

public boolean unloadModel(java.lang.String name)
Destroys the model with the specified name by unloading it from memory and therefore freeing the working memory.

Parameters:
name - The name of the model to unload as a String.
Returns:
Returns TRUE if the operation was successfull or FALSE otherwise (i.e. when no model with the specified name even existed).
